node.text: In tribute to my Irish bubba @flemshow 🙏🏾 ty for making me strong and continuing to make me stronger R.I.P til we meet again 👽🖤 I’ll always smile at the beautiful memories we have had and celebrate your life instead of holding sadness inside I’ll keep being positive and grateful i got the time i did with you 🥰🙏🏾 the beautiful part of the brain is it’s like a computer and can be reprogrammed into positive thoughts instead of reflecting negative thoughts that can cause depression. The healthiest way of grief is to still have routine and live your normal life and not just sit and dwell in sorrow because grief can be very bad for the brain When you're grieving, a flood of neurochemicals enters the brain and can be very toxic . Learn to deal with any dark situation in light and positivity just like your loved one would of wanted 🥰 love you forever bubba 👽🙏🏾
